    "description": "CDX.NA.IG.46 base correlation curve calibrated from 5 standard CDX tranche quotes (0/3%, 3/7%, 7/10%, 10/15%, 15/30% detachment points), chained on a USD-OIS discount curve and CDX-NA-IG-46 index hazard curve that are bootstrapped in the same plan. Step 1 produces the USD-OIS discount curve from deposit and IRS quotes; step 2 calibrates the CDX-NA-IG-46 index hazard curve from realistic par-spread CDS quotes (50/75/100/110/120 bp); step 3 solves for the base correlation smile. No hand-entered USD-OIS discount curve remains in initial_market \u2014 it is produced entirely from quotes. A placeholder CDX-NA-IG-46 hazard curve in initial_market is required because the credit_indices entry must reference an existing hazard curve at context-load time; step 2 overwrites it with the bootstrapped curve. A seed base_correlation curve (CDX-NA-IG-46_CORR) and credit_indices entry also remain in initial_market as required by the base correlation solver. Tranche upfront quotes are self-consistent with the chained USD-OIS + realistic CDX-IG-46 hazard market (re-derived by pricing each tranche against the bootstrapped market at seed correlations [0.10, 0.20, 0.30, 0.40, 0.55]). The base_correlation step uses use_imm_dates: true to align tranche payment dates to IMM convention. Used by 12 (full credit desk composite).",
